  "title": "Senior Mechanical Engineer / Assistant Mechanical Manager (5 days)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Assist the Project Manager and site personnel in the planning, execution, and completion of ACMV projects.</li><li>Design ACMV systems for new construction and renovation projects.</li><li>Oversee the installation and commissioning of ACMV systems to ensure proper implementation.</li><li>Troubleshoot and resolve any issues that arise with ACMV systems, ensuring optimal performance.</li><li>Collaborate with cross-functional teams, including relevant authorities, subcontractors, and on-site workers, to ensure compliance with building codes, regulations, and safety standards.</li><li>Assist in the preparation of progress payment claims and variation orders as required.</li><li>Analyze, manage, and track project costs against the budget to ensure financial adherence.</li><li>Stay updated on the latest ACMV technologies and industry best practices.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma or Degree in Mechanical Engineering or equivalent.</li><li>Relevant experience in ACMV (Air Conditioning and Mechanical Ventilation) systems for building projects.</li></ul><p><br />If interested, please submit your application to cvs@jdawms.com with your expected salary and resume.</p><p>We regret that only short-listed candidates will be contacted shortly. By submitting your application or resume, you agree to the collection, use, retention, and sharing of your personal information with potential employers for their assessment.</p><p>JDA WMS Pte Ltd | EA Personnel: Pham Thi Tuyet Mai </p><p>EA License No: 23S1595 | EA Registration No: R25127838</p>",
